I was spending my days with Hinata while investigating the records left behind by the natives.

...For the time being, I plan to return Hinata to the elf village on the full moon.

No matter how oppressed Hinata was in the elf village, the elf world was probably better for Hinata than being in the human world.

Hinata will probably live much longer than me.

If the barrier opens during the lunar eclipse, I could stay with you until my death approaches, but that's only possible if you know when the lunar eclipse will occur.

Native... When Hinata's father sent Hinata to the elf village, it was written that a lunar eclipse happened to occur.

There's no guarantee that such a coincidence will happen to me.

If I die first while waiting for the lunar eclipse, which I don't know when it will occur, I wonder what will happen to Hinata after that.

If after I die, I'll be found by an elf hunter and sold to a rich man...or there's a possibility that I'll be found by someone who hates elves.

Rich people are all perverts.

There may be people who buy elves to oppress them.

Slaves bought with money will not be treated badly. Similarly, it's hard to imagine that an elf bought with money would be cared for.

Moreover, as you can see from the people in the village where I lived, there are quite a few who abhor anything that resembles humans but is not.

If those people found out about Hinata, they would definitely be treated badly.

If that's the case, I'd better get Hinata back to the elf village before the next full moon, when I know the barrier is still open.

It's a little lonely, but it's better than leaving Hinata behind in the human world, knowing it will hurt her.

Come to think of it, did I mention that the barrier road is getting narrower?

If that's the case, I guess it would be better to get Hinata back as soon as possible, but I couldn't make that kind of decision between me and my feelings of regretting the days we spent together.

