We were speechless.

The hut... is on fire! ?

Perhaps the fire had just been started, and the flames rising were still small...but they were gradually beginning to engulf the entire hut.

"...Oh, there's a book. There."

I panicked and tried to jump into the hut, but it was already impossible to get into the hut.

It seems like it will take some time for the hut to burn down, but there is no way I can get inside.

"...W-Water. Water..."

He fetches water from the stream behind him and pours it toward the hut.

However, there was no way the fire could be subdued by that much water, and I stood there dumbfounded.

We are lucky that there are no trees around us and there is no wind today, so it looks like we will manage to avoid a forest fire.

The only thing left to do is to sit back and watch until the hut burns down.

#voice hinf0303
[Hinata] “Koya is burning, Human-san.”

Hinata, who was stunned, finally muttered.

"That's right..."

#voice hinf0304
[Hinata] "Why... is it burning?"

Did you fail to put out the fire?

No, it feels like the hut is burning from the outside, not the inside.

...If so, did someone start the fire?

Thinking that far, I was relieved.

They're from the village.

It must be so.

Of course, setting the hut on fire is something that animals cannot do, so there is no doubt that it was the work of humans.

...Damn, it's their doing.

You've come this far.

Books and other things are expensive, and even more valuable than that, but this is why people who don't understand the value of things do...!

There's nothing I can do to regain what is lost even if I grit my teeth.

It was a shame that all I could do was put my finger in my mouth.

Eventually, the flames licked the hut with their red tongues, and the sparks rose high and high.

#voice hinf0305
